news.title: Bombay HC clears path for redevelopment of 141 acres in Goregaon
news.para: The HC division bench of Chief Justice Alok Aradhe and Justice Bharati Dangre allowed a plea made in 2021 by Mhada to ensure redevelopment is done via private developers via a bidding process.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM moots TDR for redevelopment of buildings near Mumbai airport
news.para: The move will clear the decks for redevelopment of over 6,000 buildings in Vile Parle, Santacruz, Kurla and Ghatkopar, giving relief to 6-8 lakh residents, said officials.

news.title: Panchkula civic body plans to legalise some illegal colonies
news.para: The municipal corporation's proposal is to allocate 1-marla plots in Rajiv Colony, Indira Colony, Kharak Mangoli, Gandhi Colony, among other colonies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM to launch infrastructure, IT projects in Noida
news.para: During the visit, the chief minister will lay the foundation stone for Microsoft's new campus, which is spread across five acres in Sector 145. He is also set to the IT firm MAQ's new building in Sector 132 and Sify's IT campus – also spread over five acres in the same sector.

news.title: Lucknow development body to conduct forensic audit of Ansal API projects
news.para: LDA appointed a private firm to conduct the audit, which will examine the builder's property records, public facilities and the status of internal and external development works.

news.title: NGT dismisses Bhubaneswar-based builder's appeal against SEIAA
news.para: SEIAA, on Feb 18, issued the show-cause notice to the city-based realtor for violation of norms prescribed in the Environmental Certificate (EC) issued to one of its mega housing projects being executed in Kalarahanga, Bhubaneswar.

news.title: Apartments’ registration in Odisha affected for lack of OC, allotees certificate
news.para: The OC, a document that proves a building is fit to live in, was originally introduced in 1993. It remained on paper until the advent of Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA), but still, many buildings across the state do not have this very important certificate.

news.title: NCLAT issues notice to Ambuja Cements over plea filed by Sanghi Industries' ex-promoter
news.para: Alok Sanghi has moved NCLAT against an order passed by the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) on February 25, 2025 in an application under Section 95 of IBC filed by Ambuja Cements over the personal guarantee of Rs 84 crore by him.

news.title: Birla Opus plans to expand portfolio and dealer network in FY26
news.para: Aditya Birla Group entered into the decorative paints segment in February 2024 and aims to have a double-digit share and generate a gross revenue of Rs 10,000 crore within 3 years of full-scale operations.

news.title: Lucknow development body to move NCLAT against Ansal API
news.para: National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had admitted Ansal API for insolvency proceedings last week on an application filed by IL&FS Financial Services, one of the company’s financial creditors.

news.title: Chandigarh administration proposes significant increase in collector rates
news.para: The sharpest increase proposed is in the residential segment, particularly in the rural areas. In the sectoral grid of the city, the proposed growth in the collector rate ranges from 42% to 128%

news.title: Geberit expects construction sector in Europe to be stable in 2025
news.para: "Overall, the global economy will face considerable uncertainties in 2025," Geberit said. "These geopolitical and macroeconomic risks are leading to corresponding uncertainties in the building construction industry."

news.title: Ireland: Dalata Hotel Group explores potential sale, launches strategic review
news.para: The company said it had appointed Rothschild & Co as financial adviser in connection with the strategic review, adding that it is not in discussions with, or in receipt of an approach from any potential suitor.

news.title: Villagers protest against illegal land encroachment in Bamanwadi
news.para: The memorandum states that survey No. 29/B of Bamanwadi comprises five acres of govt open land for public facilities like a school, temple, residential houses, and water tanks.

news.title: Construction PMI in UK falls in February 2025
news.para: The all-sector PMI, which combines the services, manufacturing and construction sectors, fell to a 16-month low of 50.0 in February from 50.3 in January.

news.title: NCRTC invites bids for commercial, residential hubs along Delhi-Meerut Namo Bharat corridor
news.para: The selected consultants will be responsible for market research, transaction advisory, project management support, strategic planning and knowledge transfer.

news.title: China considers ending price limit for local governments buying apartments: Report
news.para: The world's second-largest economy is dealing with prolonged property sector crisis with home prices expected to drop at a faster pace this year despite measures from the government.

news.title: Protesting revenue officers resume property registration work in Punjab
news.para: The revenue officers also protested vigilance bureau action in some revenue offices, claiming such actions were "creating an atmosphere of fear".

news.title: Carpediem Capital invests Rs 100 crore in CorporatEdge
news.para: CorporatEdge plans to deploy Rs 350 crore in the next three years. It will unveil two centres, each spanning across 50,000 sq ft, in Q1 FY26 at World Trade Center (WTC) Nauroji Nagar, New Delhi, and Godrej Golf Course Road, Gurugram.
